@* ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
   File: Components/Pages/Home.razor

   PURPOSE: The root landing page at "/". Shows different content
   depending on whether the user is logged in or not.

   KEY CONCEPTS:
   • <AuthorizeView>  →  Built-in Blazor component that renders
     different child content based on authentication state.
   • <Authorized>  →  Shown only when user IS logged in.
   • <NotAuthorized>  →  Shown only when user is NOT logged in.
   ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ *@

@page "/"

<PageTitle>Puppet Fest Merch</PageTitle>

<div class="home-page">
    <header class="home-appbar" aria-label="Application navigation">
        <button type="button" class="home-menu-button" aria-label="Open menu">
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
        </button>
    </header>

    <main class="home-content" role="main">
        <section class="home-hero">
            <div class="home-logo-mark" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <h1 class="home-brand">Back Stage</h1>
            <p class="home-tagline">Inventory Management Tool</p>
            <p class="home-heading">Log in to Backstage</p>
        </section>

        <AuthorizeView>
            <Authorized>
                <section class="home-welcome-card">
                    <h2>Welcome back, @context.User.Identity?.Name!</h2>
                    <p>You are logged in.</p>
                    <a href="/dashboard" class="home-dashboard-link">Go to Dashboard →</a>
                </section>
            </Authorized>
            <NotAuthorized>
                <section class="home-auth-card">
                    <p class="home-auth-label">Ready to manage inventory?</p>
                    <div class="home-auth-actions">
                        <a href="Account/Login" class="btn btn-primary home-primary-btn">Log In</a>
                        <a href="Account/ForgotPassword" class="home-secondary-link">Forgot password?</a>
                    </div>
                </section>
            </NotAuthorized>
        </AuthorizeView>
    </main>
</div>